2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a novel bidirectional attentional recognition network, which involves natural language processing techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable model, which involves machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a model that can be trained in a weak supervised way, which involves artificial intelligence techniques. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with the problem of recognizing text from images, which is related to information retrieval.
